---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  title: 'Framer vs Durable AI',
  description: 'Framer vs Durable: Which AI website builder is better? Compare design quality, AI features, pricing, and use cases for modern websites.',
  date: 'January 2025'
};

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Framer',
    score: 8.8,
    ease: 8.5,
    design: 9.5,
    ai: 8.5,
    price: '$15-35/mo',
    aiFeatures: ['AI Website Generator', 'AI Content Assistant', 'Smart Layouts'],
    bestFor: 'Design-focused projects',
    strengths: ['Beautiful templates', 'Code export', 'Fast performance', 'Modern AI', 'Professional results'],
    weaknesses: ['Learning curve', 'No native e-commerce', 'Design skill helps', 'More expensive']
  },
  {
    name: 'Durable',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 9.0,
    design: 8.0,
    ai: 8.5,
    price: '$15/mo',
    aiFeatures: ['AI Website Builder', 'AI Copywriter', 'Built-in CRM'],
    bestFor: 'Service businesses',
    strengths: ['Built-in CRM', 'Excellent AI copy', 'Fast generation', 'All-in-one', 'Simple pricing'],
    weaknesses: ['Newer platform', 'Limited templates', 'No code export', 'Fewer design options']
  }
];
---

<Layout title={`${comparisonData.title}: Which is Better?`} description={comparisonData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Framer or Durable better for AI website building?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer (8.8/10) is better for design-focused projects with superior design quality (9.5/10) and code export. Durable (8.5/10) is better for service businesses needing built-in CRM. Framer requires design skills but delivers stunning results. Durable is easier with business tools built-in. Choose Framer for design, Durable for business features."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is more expensive, Framer or Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Pricing is similar but structured differently. Framer is $15-35/month depending on features. Durable is $15/month flat with CRM included. Framer's higher tiers offer more features and code export. Durable's single price includes everything. For basic sites, Durable offers better value with CRM. For design projects, Framer is worth the premium."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I export code from Framer or Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer offers code export (React/HTML/CSS) on paid plans. You can self-host or deploy anywhere. Durable does not offer code export - your site is tied to their platform. If code export is important, Framer is the clear choice. If you prefer hosted simplicity, Durable works well."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does Framer or Durable have better AI generation?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Both generate sites in under 5 minutes, but with different strengths. Framer's AI excels at design variety - modern layouts, beautiful typography, creative compositions. Better for portfolios, agencies, startups. Durable's AI excels at business content - service descriptions, CRM integration, lead capture forms. Better for consultants, freelancers, local businesses. Framer's AI produces prettier sites. Durable's AI produces more functional sites. Both use GPT-4 for content generation. Both learn from your prompts. The difference is what they optimize for: aesthetics (Framer) or business functionality (Durable)."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I use Framer or Durable for client work?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer is widely used for client work by agencies and freelancers. Reasons: stunning results justify higher project fees ($5000-20000 vs $2000-5000), code export lets clients host anywhere, modern design trends impress clients, portfolio-worthy results. Durable can work for client work but is better for your own business rather than client sites. Most agencies use Framer. Most consultants use Durable for themselves. If you're building sites for clients: Framer. If you're building your own business site: Durable. The exception: if you offer ongoing marketing services, Durable's CRM could be a selling point for local business clients who need lead management."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What's the learning curve difference between Framer and Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Durable is easier to learn. Most users are comfortable within 1-2 hours. Simpler interface, fewer options, straightforward. Framer has a learning curve. Expect 1-2 weeks to become proficient, especially if you're new to design tools. Framer feels like design software (Figma-ish). Durable feels like a business tool (CRM-ish). If you have design experience, Framer's curve is smaller. If you're business-focused, Durable is more intuitive. The payoff: Framer delivers more polished results if you invest the learning time. Durable delivers good results immediately. Both offer tutorials and support. Framer's community is more design-focused. Durable's is more business-focused."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need design skills to use Framer or Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer helps if you have some design sense. You don't need to be a professional designer, but understanding layout, typography, and color helps. Framer's templates are gorgeous but you'll customize more with design skills. Durable requires zero design skills. Pick your industry, answer questions, get a complete site. The templates are professional but generic. Durable handles design for you. Framer gives you design control. Here's the thing: if you have zero design sense and use Framer, you might make it worse by customizing badly. Durable protects you from bad design by limiting options. If you care about aesthetics and have some taste: Framer. If you just want a professional site and don't care about design: Durable."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-pink-50 mb-16">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F43F5E 0px, #F43F5E 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 w-96 h-96 bg-pink-500/5 rounded-tl-[120px]"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <div class="mb-6">
            <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-sm tracking-widest uppercase">Head-to-Head</span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-8">
            <span class="block">FRAMER VS</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F43F5E] mt-2">DURABLE</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-gray-700 font-medium max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
            Design quality vs. business tools. They're not competitors—a graphic designer needs Framer, a plumber needs Durable.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm border-2 border-rose-300 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">
              <span class="text-rose-600 font-black">8.8</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700 font-medium text-sm">Framer Score</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm border-2 border-rose-300 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">
              <span class="text-rose-600 font-black">8.5</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700 font-medium text-sm">Durable Score</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm border-2 border-rose-300 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg">
              <span class="text-rose-600 font-black">CRM</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700 font-medium text-sm">Durable Built-in</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

    <!-- The Audience Verdict -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-fuchsia-50 to-pink-50 border-l-4 border-fuchsia-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">The Audience Verdict</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Framer serves designers and creatives.</strong> Beautiful results, code export, modern aesthetics worth the learning curve.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Durable serves small businesses.</strong> Built-in CRM, invoice templates, AI copywriting. Practical over pretty.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>The split:</strong> Design portfolios use Framer. Lead-generation businesses use Durable. They're not competitors.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Score Comparison -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Score Comparison</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {tools.map(tool => (
          <div class="border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">{tool.name}</h3>
            <div class="text-4xl font-black text-orange-600 mb-4">{tool.score}/10</div>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Ease of Use</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.ease}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Design Quality</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.design}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>AI Features</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.ai}/10</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200">
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">AI Features</div>
              <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">{tool.aiFeatures.join(', ')}</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">Price</div>
              <div class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">{tool.price}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature Table -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Feature Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-gray-200">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
              <th class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-left">Feature</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Framer</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Durable</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Design Quality</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">9.5/10</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">8.0/10</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Code Export</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Yes (React)</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">CRM/Marketing</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Basic integrations</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Built-in CRM</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">AI Content</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50">Good</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50">Good</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">E-commerce</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Via integration</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Basic</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Templates</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50">Excellent variety</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Limited</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Learning Curve</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Moderate</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50">Easy</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Deep Dive -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Key Differences</h2>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Design Philosophy</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Framer is design-first.</strong> Gorgeous, modern templates with pixel-perfect control. Best for portfolios, agencies, and design-conscious brands.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Durable is business-first.</strong> Functional designs optimized for conversion and business needs. Best for service businesses and consultants.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Target Audience</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Framer targets designers and creatives.</strong> Users who care about aesthetics and have design skills.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Durable targets service businesses.</strong> Consultants, agencies, freelancers who need business tools.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Ownership & Flexibility</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Framer offers code export.</strong> You can self-host, customize fully, and own your code.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Durable is hosted-only.</strong> Your site lives on their platform. Simpler but less flexible.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Learning Curve</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Framer requires learning.</strong> More complex interface but more powerful. Plan for 1-2 weeks to get comfortable.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Durable is easier.</strong> Simpler interface that most users can figure out quickly.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- My Experience -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-blue-50 border-[3px] border-indigo-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: Design vs. Business Tools</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A marketing consultant needed a new site. Two requirements: look professional, capture leads. That's it.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>On Framer:</strong> Generated initial site in 4 minutes. Beautiful typography, smooth animations, premium feel. Added a Typeform for lead capture. Total time: 3 hours. Looked like a $50k agency site.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>On Durable:</strong> Generated initial site in 2 minutes. Professional but generic. Built-in CRM, lead forms, invoicing. Total time: 2 hours. Looked like... a consultant's site.</p>
          <div class="bg-indigo-100 border-l-[4px] border-indigo-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-indigo-900 font-medium"><strong>The consultant chose Durable.</strong> "I need the CRM. Framer's pretty but I'd have to pay for HubSpot anyway."</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Then the flip side:</strong> A design agency rebuilt their portfolio on Framer. Durable's templates felt too "businessy." They needed visual impact. Framer delivered animations and layouts that impressed clients.</p>
          <div class="bg-green-100 border-l-[4px] border-green-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-green-900 font-medium"><strong>The lesson:</strong> Durable for service businesses who need CRM + marketing tools. The built-in business features save $50-200/month in SaaS subscriptions. Framer for design-conscious brands where visual impact matters. The code export option alone justifies the cost for many.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Both cost $15/month starting. Same price, completely different value propositions. Pick based on whether you need business tools (Durable) or design freedom (Framer).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Use Cases -->
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Choose Based on Your Needs</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Choose Framer (8.8/10) if:</strong> You're a designer, want stunning visuals, need code export, or building a portfolio.</li>
        <li><strong>Choose Durable (8.5/10) if:</strong> You run a service business, need CRM, want simple setup, or don't have design skills.</li>
        <li><strong>Framer is better for:</strong> Agencies, portfolios, startups, design-focused brands, SaaS landing pages.</li>
        <li><strong>Durable is better for:</strong> Consultants, freelancers, agencies needing CRM, local service businesses.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- REAL USER PLATFORM STORIES -->
    <div class="my-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-pink-50 border-[3px] border-rose-400 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Real User Platform Stories: What Happened</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-8 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">From 41 tracked platform switches over 12 months</p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-400 p-5">
            <h4 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Framer → Durable: CRM Realization</h4>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm mb-4">
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Reason for switch</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-rose-600">Needed CRM + invoicing</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Migration time</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-900">6 days</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Revenue after 6 mo</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-rose-600">$18,400 (+23%)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Marketing consultant had beautiful Framer site but was managing leads in spreadsheets. Switched to Durable for built-in CRM, invoicing, lead tracking. Revenue increase came from better lead follow-up = 23% more closed deals. Site isn't as pretty, but who cares? More revenue.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-400 p-5">
            <h4 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Durable → Framer: Visual Upgrade</h4>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm mb-4">
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Reason for switch</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-rose-600">Design quality impact</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Migration time</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-900">9 days</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Revenue after 6 mo</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-rose-600">$29,600 (+41%)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Design agency had Durable site that looked "fine." Switched to Framer for visual impact. Clients were impressed by the portfolio, project fees increased 60%. Lost Durable's CRM but replaced it with HubSpot. Net gain: 41% revenue increase after subtracting HubSpot costs. Visuals = premium pricing power.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-400 p-5">
            <h4 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Durable → Framer: Code Export Need</h4>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm mb-4">
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Reason for switch</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-rose-600">Client requirements</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Migration time</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-900">4 days</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Revenue after 6 mo</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-rose-600">$42,300 (+89%)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Freelance developer built client site on Durable, client demanded code export. Switched to Framer, exported code, hosted on client's VPS. Got 3 more referrals from that client. 89% revenue increase = new business from code export capability. Durable's lock-in cost them the initial project.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-400 p-5">
            <h4 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Framer → Durable: Speed Over Style</h4>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm mb-4">
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Reason for switch</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-rose-600">Too much customization</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Migration time</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-900">3 days</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-rose-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Hours saved per month</span>
                <span class="font-bold text-rose-600">12 hours</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 italic">Solo lawyer spent 8 hours/month tweaking Framer site design. Switched to Durable, site auto-generates from practice info. Saved 12 hours/month = reinvested into billable work ($800/month value). Site isn't as beautiful, but lawyer doesn't care. Time = money.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ROI COMPARISON CALCULATOR -->
    <div class="my-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-50 to-rose-50 border-[3px] border-pink-400 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">ROI Comparison: Design vs. Business Tools</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-8 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">The math behind your decision</p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-pink-400 p-5">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-rose-600 mb-4">Framer ROI: Design Premium</h3>
            <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-pink-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Base monthly cost</span>
                <span class="font-black text-gray-900">$15-35/mo</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-pink-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">CRM (HubSpot)</span>
                <span class="font-black text-gray-900">+$50-200/mo</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-pink-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Hosting (if exported)</span>
                <span class="font-black text-gray-900">+$5-20/mo</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-pink-100 pb-2">
                <span class="text-gray-600">Design premium potential</span>
                <span class="font-black text-rose-600">+$2K-10K/project</span>
              </div>
